Article.ArticleTitle: Guttiferones K and L, antiproliferative compounds of Rheedia calcicola from the Madagascar rain forest.

AbstractText: Bioassay-guided fractionation of the ethanol extract obtained from the fruits of Rheedia calcicola led to the isolation of two new guttiferone analogues, guttiferones K (1) and L (16-hydroxyguttiferone K) (2). The structures of 1 and 2 were established on the basis of extensive interpretation of one- and two-dimensional NMR spectroscopic data. Both compounds were tested for their antiproliferative activity against the A2780 human ovarian cancer cell line.
